snippet.textDisplay: Hey, just a quick comment about the cat allergy thing. If Jack can't answer this or has talked about it in an old video, how did he become aware of his cat allergy? Was it just the sneezing/coughing around cats or was it from a blood test? I ask because I had blood tests saying that I was severely allergic to pet dander. But I had no reaction to it. No runny, itchy eyes, no sneezing, no coughing... nothing. I had to get rid of my beloved dog as a child because a test showed that I was allergic. But I'm thinking now that it was dust related. I've never had a direct reaction to being around animals. Even now, I'm living with three cats and it doesn't bother me.
